          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-01-11T16:28:07Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Coretta Scott King Mid-Decade Redistricting Prohibition Act of 2019</strong></p> <p> This bill prohibits any state whose congressional districts have been redistricted after a decennial census from carrying out another redistricting until after the next apportionment of Representatives following a decennial census, unless a court requires such state to conduct a subsequent redistricting to comply with the Constitution or enforce the Voting Rights Act of 1965. </p> <p>The bill is applicable to any congressional redistricting which occurs after the regular decennial census conducted during 2020. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-01-03T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
